******
[2] Cholera - Ghana (Upper East Region)
Date:Tue 21 Oct 2014
Source: Citi FM Online [edited]
http://www.citifmonline.com/2014/10/21/3-die-in-upper-east-cholera-outbreak/


An increase in the number of cholera cases in the Upper East Region has resulted in 3 deaths so far in the region. 10 out of the 13 districts in the region Bawku in the Upper East region are on the increase with 3 people dead so far. The region has recorded over 100 cholera cases in 10 out of its 13 districts. The rate of increase has alarmed health officials in the 3 regions of the North that were relatively cholera-free until a few weeks ago.

The deputy public health director in the region, Dr Mensah Afful, said that they are doing all they can to bring the situation under control. "We have had 127 cases, and we have done damage cost. Prior to Bawku, we had quite a number of districts also having cholera at a point in time, but several of them have been contained except a couple of them in Bawku and Pusiga," he told Citi News. "The number of [cholera cases] we have had is not as substantial as it was in the last 2 days when the incident began."

