******
[3] Cholera - Ghana (Brong Ahafo Region)
Date: Sun 26 Oct 2014
Source: Citi FM Online [edited]
http://www.citifmonline.com/2014/10/26/cholera-one-dead-34-more-infected-in-ba/


About 34 cholera cases have been recorded in the Goaso government hospital in the Brong Ahafo region, while one person has died as a result of the outbreak of the disease. All the cases were recorded in the month of October 2014.

The latest cases of cholera have been attributed to the poor domestic and personal hygiene practices observed by residents in the area, according to the municipal health director at the hospital, Duut Berima. In an interview with Citi News, Duut Berima urged residents to observe good personal hygiene to prevent a further spread of the disease. He also emphasized the need for residents in the area to be educated on effective ways of adhering to such practices.

The Greater Accra region has recorded the highest number of cases so far, but the rate of infection has declined.

[byline: Marian Efe Ansah]

