******
[4] Cholera - Ghana (Eastern Region)
Date: Mon 20 October 2014
Source: Ghana Broadcasting Corporation [edited]
http://www.gbcghana.com/1.1874389


Despite the interventions being put in place by the Ghana Health Service, government and other health partners, cholera cases are still rising in the Eastern Region. The current data collected from the Regional Disease Control Unit of the Ghana Health Services shows that 1723 cases of cholera have been recorded in 16 districts of the region with 6 deaths.

Nsawam-Adoagyiri Municipality leads by 492 cases with one death. West Akyem Municipality follows with 439 cases but no deaths, while Akwapim North Municipality comes next with 203 cases and 2 deaths. New Juaben Municipality takes the 4th position with 214 cases.

